Detailed Description

Encapsulation of the various methods that all xxxConfig objects must implement.

For accessing the individual items of a list within a configuration object, we use the following conventions (e.g., for accessing the TemplateConfig list within a CollectorConfig, "Aaa" would be "Template"):

getAaaConfigList()
gets the list as an ArrayList.
getAaaConfigIterator()
gets the list as a ListIterator.
getAaaConfigListLength()
gets the length of the list.
getAaaConfigAt(int i)
gets the ith element
getAaaConfigById(...)
gets the element identified by the "id" (usually, but not always, an int).

These methods are safe in the sense that they will work if the contained list is null.
